{"ts": "2026-06-09T00:04:02.790312+00:00", "update": {"tools": {"messages": [{"type": "tool", "data": {"content": [{"type": "text", "text": "successfully downloaded text file (SHA: 4c72cbcde1d4f9e16974aab9c35e7cfd4d033fad)", "id": "lc_2a9d5a3f-e591-4663-8633-e4ed7caff859"}, {"type": "text", "text": "\"\"\"Load optional gwc configuration from ./.gwcrc.\"\"\"\nfrom __future__ import annotations\n\nimport tomllib\nfrom pathlib import Path\n\n\ndef load_config(path: Path | None = None) -> dict:\n    path = path or Path(\".gwcrc\")\n    if not path.exists():\n        return {}\n    with path.open(\"rb\") as f:\n        return tomllib.load(f)\n", "id": "lc_ebaf40e4-0a69-49dc-9b6e-9a1140b39615"}], "additional_kwargs": {}, "response_metadata": {}, "type": "tool", "name": "get_file_contents", "id": "fa65a347-2dc0-4592-be65-4294e12cdfd9", "tool_call_id": "call_e949f4e149e84d2c97261cfc", "artifact": null, "status": "success"}}]}}}
{"ts": "2026-06-09T00:04:19.200113+00:00", "update": {"model": {"messages": [{"type": "ai", "data": {"content": "Based on my exploration of the repository, here's what I found:\n\n## Installed Command-Line Tool\n\nThe package installs a command-line tool called **`gwc`** (Git Workflow Companion), as declared in `pyproject.toml`:\n\n```toml\n[project.scripts]\ngwc = \"gwc.cli:main\"\n```\n\nNote: The README mentions that `gwc` is being phased out in favor of `git-wc` as of version 0.1.x, though the old name still works.\n\n## What `gwc` Currently Does\n\n`gwc` is a small Python CLI that wraps day-to-day git workflows for solo developers. It provides **three subcommands**:\n\n1. **`gwc status-summary`** — Prints a one-line summary of the current branch state, including:\n   - Current branch name\n   - Ahead/behind count vs. its tracked upstream (if any)\n   - Number of staged, unstaged, and untracked files\n\n2. **`gwc branch-name <issue-number> <short-slug>`** — Generates and prints a conventional branch name for an issue (e.g., `issue-42-add-login`). It does *not* create the branch — just prints the name for you to copy or pipe into `git checkout -b`.\n\n3. **`gwc clean-merged`** — Lists local branches that are fully merged into `main` and can optionally delete them. By default runs in dry-run mode (printing what *would* be deleted); pass `--apply` to actually delete.\n\n## What It Does NOT Do\n\n`gwc` intentionally avoids network operations (`push`, `pull`, `fetch`, `clone`), rebasing/history rewriting, and credential management — it's purely a local workflow helper.\n\n## Configuration\n\nIt optionally reads settings from a `.gwcrc` file (TOML) in the repository root for customizing the branch prefix and protected branch list.", "additional_kwargs": {"refusal": null}, "response_metadata": {"token_usage": {"completion_tokens": 421, "prompt_tokens": 7486, "total_tokens": 7907, "completion_tokens_details": {"accepted_prediction_tokens": null, "audio_tokens": 0, "reasoning_tokens": 12, "rejected_prediction_tokens": null, "image_tokens": 0}, "prompt_tokens_details": {"audio_tokens": 0, "cached_tokens": 7232, "cache_write_tokens": 0, "video_tokens": 0}, "cost": 0, "is_byok": true, "cost_details": {"upstream_inference_cost": 0.0005027952, "upstream_inference_prompt_cost": 0.0001365252, "upstream_inference_completions_cost": 0.00036627}}, "model_provider": "openai", "model_name": "xiaomi/mimo-v2.5-pro-20260422", "system_fingerprint": null, "id": "gen-1780963443-CiiGHTJvYU9zzbRylSNO", "finish_reason": "stop", "logprobs": null}, "type": "ai", "name": null, "id": "lc_run--019ea9b1-8067-7b73-998f-20d9209b8c54-0", "tool_calls": [], "invalid_tool_calls": [], "usage_metadata": {"input_tokens": 7486, "output_tokens": 421, "total_tokens": 7907, "input_token_details": {"audio": 0, "cache_read": 7232}, "output_token_details": {"audio": 0, "reasoning": 12}}}}]}}}
